Very  spiritual , timeless  mind ,sans  frontiers (without boundaries) ,global citizen, live in real-time (the very moment), zero ego, unconditional  love for  all , and  hope  this makes  sense to you.

Sounds unreal AA?A??? fiction, strange, Its alright, not everyone expected  to  understand  it, there  are 6  bn  folks on planet earth  and have same number of perception about life based on their  experience  and  to the best  of their  ability .

Looking  for  one  special  who has  risen  above the myopic vision of life, understands & realized that  life is just a short journey through  time & space  of  planet  earth , and the  best way to utilize  this opportunity is to live in peace ,harmony,&  happiness , live life  the best possible way we can in total  awareness & mindful of  others  that their peace  is not disturbed. Am I a dreamer..? may be ? for me life itself  is a dream -
(as in dream nothing really happening  but  still seems  so real where all senses and emotions are active and responding  but when you wake up you realize  ,whoops  it was just a dream).

Is that  you ? I am looking  for, one who is in awaken  state  and  sees life in its true &  absolute  form . carries  no baggage from past , are you naturally  blissful from  within , are you child  like yet wise & mature as situation  demands . you fall in category  of soul mate. have no illusion  about yourself.  All I would say is, you are priceless.

I am not a preacher  of poverty neither  an advocate  for materialism ,believe  in middle path (what ever   comes  naturally without hurting anybody or self) the buzz words  are  content, happy, blissful, these are the  most  precious things in life.

I am on this site for no particular reason, just  inspired  by M.J. 
AA?A? you are not alone AA?A?, and scientific theory AA?A? are we alone in the universeAA?A? just  curious ,is there some one I can relate to who is think & feel  alike, I would  like to share  rest of my life with you.

Like every one else chasing the rainbow or in search of Eldorado (city of gold), wish you all the best, may life unfolds for you in best possible way,  the  way  best suited  for you.

Blessed  be,"

being"", does not belong to any race ,creed belief,sect,geographic location ,any sort of pride , as these are nothing but temporary stage props to be with you till the show lasts . all you have to be is simple human being.

1.	About Self
     R  is fair, tall, and very personable. He is well mannered, with a good sense of humour, and a cosmopolitan outlook. He is of a friendly disposition and helpful nature. He has varied interests and very good social qualities, with a large circle of friends. He was educated in Bangalore, and, after PUC, in  Delhi, where his father was posted with the Central Government.  He took his MBA from IMT, Ghaziabad, and worked in Delhi for some years. He can speak Hindi fluently. He has traveled abroad on several occasions.
     He has worked in Delhi and Chennai, and is now employed in Bangalore where he holds a senior management position.
    He is divorced  by mutual consent from his first wife. 
     He has a younger sister, who is married and lives in Hong Kong. Her husband holds a senior position in  a bank. They have a daughter.
     He is widely read and has a large circle of friends.  
                       
2.Family Details
      His father retired from the IAS, after holding responsible positions. His uncle (elder brother), also from the same service, held high positions in the country. One maternal uncle was also in the IAS, and headed the administration in Kerala. Another was CMD of a large public sector undertaking. His family are Tamil Brahmins who have settled in Bangalore since long, where his parents now live in their own house. The family combines traditional values with a modern outlook. column1: This is the second time I've come to this page to write about myself. The first time I had no idea what to write. I then started asking people what I was like and got a lot of opinions. Most were similar, so I'll write them down. People say my main asset is my sense of humour (Ya, right. I'm sure you heard that before. This time it's true. ) and my happy attitude towards life. I feel life is to short to take seriously, but long enough to plan ahead for a future. I also believe money isn't the end all of life, I believe in God, in all things beautiful, people(I still think there's hope for humanity), my partner and most of all I believe in GOOD FOOD (I owned 2 American-Italian restaurants). I am a creature of my environment. I feel at home in the lap of luxury of a 5 star hotel or in a one room shack (provided its on a Goan beach: ) Just kiddin'). So in a nutshell I'm happy, easy going, chilled, peaceful, laid back yet ambition, hard working and goal oriented. A little about my past: Born U.S., 4th std to Bsc Bangalore, back to U.S. for Engg, owned Greek American restaurant in U.S., sold business, moved to India 1993 to be with parents, married 1994, opened restaurant in chennai, divorced 1999, sold restaurants2008, have communications firm till date. This is the Readers Digest version. Full version available for perusal after sacrificing pinky finger. Well, I guess I finally got through this. I hope I pass the test. Looking for: Enough about me for now. Lets get to you. I obviously gel with people having traits similar to mine. But I think a partner should be different in ways as to keep the balance (something like yin & yan). As for looks, if you think you're beautiful, not only on the outside but mainly on the inside, then you are (no cliche, I mean it. ),,"My Family: What can I say? My parents are conmen, my brother a hustler and my sister a jewel thief. Just pulling a fast one. It's been too long since I wrote or said something stupid. My parents and sibling are wonderful people, just like me (think I have an ego?). If it matters to you what they do, then here it is- my Dad is a father of 3, a retired director of a defense research establishment, mother housewife or should I say a 'stay at home mom' and a great cook, my brother a software professional (got to have at least one in the family) and a father of one and lastly my sister an accounting/software person and mother of 3. That's it. Hope you like them. ",32 to 43,28 Jun 1963,,India,,Slim,Doesn't Matter,,,,,,Wheatish ,Doesn't Matter,Self,BE B.Tech (Engineering),"50 yrs, 5ft 9in,

I am born in Malaysia, educated in Australia and live in Singapore. My grandparents are from India.

I work for a large American MNC.

I am not perfect by any means, I am honest (sometimes a little direct!), hard working, and have done quite well form myself thru God's grace, hard work and a little luck.

I am well traveled, my work takes me around the Asia Pacific and the USA.

I am guided by my conscience and I am God fearing. I have traveled around India extensively, and really enjoy Indian food, music and culture.

I am concerned about the environment, and love wildlife sanctuaries and National Parks. I used to play lots of sport in my youth - badminton, squash, hockey, tennis. Nowadays I go for long brisk walks to get my required cardiovascular exercise.

I try and do good and give charity, as I believe good things happen to kind people. 

I love kids and sadly don't have any yet - willing to give myself another chance at happiness. 

I have a close knit family, my late father believed in spending lots of time with us and I hope to do the same if blessed with a good wife.

I respect elders, and am not ostentatious.

I believe in God, though I don't wear my religious convistions on my sleeve.

I love travel, the calming effects of North Indian classical music, and chilling out with good friends.

I'm fairly health conscious, and in fairly good health and exercise quite regularly.

I try to be happy. 

I wish you good luck in your search for happiness.,"Looking for a soft spoken calm, kind hearted, cultured and educated lady, who wants to have kids of our own. If you already have kids, thats fine, I will do my best to love them as my own and provide well for them.
